Nike Popoola The Chief Executive Officer, Financial Reporting Council of Nigeria, Mr Daniel Asapokhai, has said it is finalising work on the Audit Regulation 2020 to improve investor confidence and ensure quality accounting standard in the country. He said this during a webinar titled ‘The strategic assessment of Financial Reporting Council’s draft audit regulation’ on Saturday. “Today’s exercise, which is one of the steps towards finalising the audit regulation, is strategic in the quest for the realisation of the council’s mission statement to bring utmost confidence to investors, reputation to oversight and ensure quality in accounting, auditing, actuarial, valuation and cooperate governance standards and non-financial reporting issues,” he said. Asapokhai was represented by the Deputy Director/Head (Directorate of Accounting Standards Public Sector), Financial Reporting Council of Nigeria, Dr Iheanyi Anyahara. Copyright PUNCH.
